hange. This discussion of reform strategies will interest not only those who are concerned with excellence and equity in education but also those who wish to form successful coalitions and challenge existing state policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEducationzUnited StatesxFinance. 0aEducation, UrbanzUnited States. 0aEducational equalizationzUnited States. 0aSchool management and organizationzUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh1 aAugenblick, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernstein, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCittell, Marilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoertz, Margaret E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorcoran, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortez, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarling, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGittell, Marilyn J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGittell, Marilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHershkoff, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcKenna, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Donald R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoos, Peter D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScovronick, Nathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSexton, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStone, Clarence N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula